  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nCurrently (when doing a fast sync) it generates the transactions trie manually (using `make_trie_root_and_nodes()`) and persists that to the DB, so we don't get the DB entries that allow us to lookup the block of a given tx by hash.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nWe could redesign `ChainSyncer` so that it uses `ChainDB.persist_block()`, but that would certainly affect performance significantly because that trie generation would be done in the DB process and that is quite expensive.\r\n\r\nAnother option would be to duplicate (or refactor) parts of `persist_block()` so that `ChainSyncer` calls `ChainDB._add_transaction_to_canonical_chain()` after it calls `ChainDB.persist_header()`\r\n\r\n",
